 Message ()
Message

Three kind of Message exist. The ActiveMessage and WriteAndSignal and AllocateWriteAndSignal protocols. Message is base class for these kinds of message. A message is a formatted sequence of bytes. The interpretation of the sequence on the receiving site is of the responsability of the service called. The first bytes always contains :

  • Net::Header : the header of all kind of message If the message is an ActiveMessage, then the next bytes should be interpreted as
  • Net::HeaderAM : the caracteristic of the Header for Active Message

Since the network support aggregation of message, on the receiving side, a new incomming message is an aggregation of message and begins by an AggrHeader.
